The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 20 February is 221,775 (25,560.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 15 February, there were 6,823 new confirmed cases (786.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 08 February, there were 8,908 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 23% (2,085 fewer cases).
